</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Edita Morris</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:142px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Edita_Morris.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Edita_Morris.png/140px-Edita_Morris.png" width="140" height="175" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Edita_Morris.png/210px-Edita_Morris.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Edita_Morris.png/280px-Edita_Morris.png 2x" data-file-width="570" data-file-height="713" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Edita_Morris.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
Edita Morris</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Edith (Edita) Dagmar Emilia Morris</b>, born <i>Toll</i> (5 March 1902 – 15 March 1988) was a <a href="/wiki/Swedish-American" title="Swedish-American" class="mw-redirect">Swedish-American</a> writer and political activist. </p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
<h2>Contents</h2>
</div>
